<br>
Whether it is getting more levels, getting a group together to kill mobs for the uber drops (thus outfitting yourself and any guild members with you), or just helping guild mates on a quest or whatever.<br>
<br>
I think the number of Mithril Hearts that want you to do something that you don't enjoy and is horribly expensive is pretty low.<br>
<br>
If you find any that think you should invest the time and plat for a skill you don't have any fun with, I suggest that you make them a deal.  You will spend the time, if they invest the plat.<br>
<br>
Although EverQuest and the guild is a large part of my life, it is still just a game.  If you start spending huge amounts of time and energy on something like a trade skill and don't enjoy it, then you are a huge candidate for burn out.  keep happy and kick arse on stuff you enjoy and leave the tradeskills to people that enjoy them.<br>
<br>
I enjoy jewelry, but decided that it was way too expensive (both in plat and experience lost due to time spent on the skill) and was preventing me from getting the gear that would make my characters more useful to the guild.<br>
<br>
In the grand scheme of things, a few deaths without rezzes can cost a lot of lost experience, but they are nothing when compared to exp lost due to trade skills sucking up hours of play time  :-)<br>
<br>
